{
  "stem": "10353.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the SS scooped it up, but we managed to save a few and it was circulated in the various barracks.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And needless to say, it gave us some encouragement, because it gave us an idea how close the Allies are towards us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, the situation became more-- more adverse, because the population of the camp started to increase very rapidly.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They started to bring in [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] people from other camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And while this camp originally held about 20,000, 25,000 people, it rapidly increased to 40,000 to 50,000 to 60,000, to as high as the rumor was that there are 120,000 people now in the camp.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was a heavy, heavy load.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They couldn't feed us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that little bit of coffee that they gave us in the-- in the morning, around 8 o'clock or 9 o'clock after-- after it depends when the appell was finished, that either didn't come at all, or it came in-- in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And similarly with the turnip soup, either it-- it didn't come anymore at 1 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It came either 4 o'clock in the afternoon or 6 o'clock at night or 12 o'clock midnight, and-- or it came the following morning at 4 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the famine was so huge that I remember those faces that, instead of going to lie down and-- and just stretch out, they would be leaning against the pillars of the-- wooden pillars of the-- of the barrack with that little can or that little dish that they may have had, waiting for that little bit of soup to come in.",
      "word_count": 62
    }
  ],
